Which out

Source: R/counters.R
which_out.Rd

Return the values of x that are %out% of the vector y.

which_out(x, y, na.rm = TRUE, ignore.case = FALSE)

Arguments

x

A vector to check.
y

A vector to compare against.
na.rm

logical; Should NA be ignored?
ignore.case

logical; if FALSE, the pattern matching is case sensitive and if TRUE, case is ignored during matching.

Value

The elements of x that are %out% y.

Details

x[which(x %out% y)]

See also

Other counting wrappers: count_diff(), count_in(), count_na(), count_out(), count_vec(), na_in(), na_out(), na_rep(), prop_distinct(), prop_in(), prop_na(), prop_out(), which_in()

Examples

which_out(c("VT", "DC", NA), state.abb)
#> [1] "DC"
